The paper discusses the training of deep neural networks (DNNs) and their applications in computer vision, speech processing, and text analysis, which are all subfields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on weight initialization techniques for DNNs, which falls under the category of optimization and learning in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on practical datasets, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the vanishing/exploding gradient problem, which is a common issue in neural networks and falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes a data-dependent initialization technique, which could also fall under the category of data mining (cs.DM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
